---
import '@fontsource-variable/space-grotesk';
import '@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/400.css';
import '@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/600.css';
import '../../styles/echo-standalone.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content="ECHO standalone page: human-sounding bilingual text-to-speech with masculine, feminine, and non-gendered voice renditions." />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#5ba7ff" />
    <title>ECHO | Standalone Voice Surface</title>
  </head>
  <body class="echo-standalone">
    <div class="echo-shell">
      <header class="echo-header">
        <a class="echo-brand" href="/echo/">
          <span class="echo-mark">ECHO</span>
          <span class="echo-tagline">Standalone Voice Surface</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="echo-nav" aria-label="ECHO navigation">
          <a href="/projects/echo/">Project details</a>
          <a href="/projects/">All projects</a>
          <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <main class="echo-main">
        <section class="echo-hero">
          <p class="echo-eyebrow">Text-to-Speech</p>
          <h1>Natural bilingual voices for English and French.</h1>
          <p>
            ECHO is a dedicated text-to-speech surface focused on human-like delivery: rhythm, pacing, phrasing,
            intonation, and connected-speech behavior. It supports masculine, feminine, and non-gendered rendition
            profiles built from the same phonology and prosody framework.
          </p>
          <div class="echo-actions">
            <a class="echo-button primary" href="/projects/echo/">View ECHO project record</a>
            <a class="echo-button secondary" href="mailto:martinlepage.ai@gmail.com">Request voice testing access</a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="echo-grid" aria-label="Rendition profiles">
          <article class="echo-card">
            <h2>Masculine</h2>
            <p>Lower-centered range with stable clarity and controlled energy for long-form narration.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Balanced breath pacing across phrase groups</li>
              <li>Clear consonant edges without harshness</li>
              <li>Natural sentence-fall behavior</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="echo-card">
            <h2>Feminine</h2>
            <p>Brighter resonance and agile contour motion while keeping intelligibility grounded.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Flexible phrase shaping for emphasis</li>
              <li>Smooth transitions in connected speech</li>
              <li>Consistent tempo under longer passages</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="echo-card">
            <h2>Non-gendered</h2>
            <p>Neutral resonance profile designed to avoid forced gender cues while sounding human.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Center-weighted pitch strategy</li>
              <li>Low-stereotype timbre balancing</li>
              <li>Clean bilingual articulation targets</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </section>

        <section class="echo-lines">
          <h3>Voice naturalness targets</h3>
          <p><code>English</code> “I can confirm the review is scheduled for tomorrow morning.”</p>
          <p><code>French</code> “Je peux confirmer que la revue est prévue demain matin.”</p>
          <p>
            Each line is tuned for realistic human pacing rather than robotic uniform timing, with pronunciation
            variation constrained by the selected rendition profile.
          </p>
        </section>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
